{
  "text": "There are several reasons that have long hindered the undertaking of such studies. One of them, perhaps minor, is the technical difficulty in undertaking case\u00b1control studies of late or early death, irrespective of the cause. Another, far more important, is the difficulty of assessing, or indeed defining, what is meant by a dietary exposure pattern. The task did not become easier when it was recognised that full interpretability of dietary intakes requires the simultaneous assessment of total energy intake [CITATION_1] .",
